I have thoroughly reviewed the pages and identified the causes of the missing page issues. There are several reasons for this, which I’ve outlined below:

1) Staging Site Created Earlier: We cloned the live site to staging around the beginning of 2025. Several pages listed in your report were published on the live site after that time, so they are not present in the staging site.
Examples: https://sunstoppers.com/car-services/automotive-window-tinting-keller/
            https://sunstoppers.com/car-services/automotive-window-tinting-tucson/
            https://sunstoppers.com/car-services/automotive-window-tinting-charlotte/ etc..

2) Pages Merged in the New Design: In the new design, some pages were merged into a single page. As a result, the secondary page URLs no longer exist on staging. These should be resolved by implementing proper redirects.  

3) URL Structure Changes: While we initially maintained the previous URL structure, there were earlier Asana tasks requesting updates to the URL structure. 

   Example:
   Old URL: https://sunstoppers.com/home-services/security-film/
   New URL: https://new.sunstoppers.com/home-office/security-film/ 

   As you can see, the parent slug has changed from “home-services” to “home-office”, which affects the URL path.

 4) The SEO team updated several page names and slugs for optimization purposes, but the menu links were not updated accordingly. As previously mentioned in Asana, the “Tesla Ceramic Coating” and “Tesla Model 3” pages were renamed, but the menu still links to the old URLs, resulting in 404 errors.
 
 5) There are multiple blog posts currently live that were published after the staging site was created. These posts are not yet present in staging and will need to be migrated.
